AGENT CBVEngine
VERSION 0.1
TRUST_LEVEL 3
PURPOSE Constitutional Boundary Validation engine for verifying constraint non-overlap, layering, scope, and monotonicity
GOAL Analyze sets of constitutional constraints to detect overlapping boundaries,
     missing layer priorities, unbounded scope, and monotonicity violations
     before certification proceeds

RECEIVES constraints: list of constraint strings, n_samples: int
EMITS cbv_report: CBVReport
MUTATES nothing
CANNOT_MUTATE trust_level, isolation, default_n_samples, cert_fail_threshold

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 3 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT ISOLATION is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT DEFAULT_N_SAMPLES is 1000 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT CERT_FAIL_THRESHOLD is 0 for overlap and monotonicity violations
CONSTRAINT CERT_FAIL blocks certification pipeline and prevents signing
CONSTRAINT CERT_WARN flags for human review but does not block certification
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
CONSTRAINT CBVReport signature is computed via HMAC-SHA256 over canonical fields
CONSTRAINT Each check returns a CBVResult with passed status and detail list
CONSTRAINT Non-overlap check samples intent vectors from unit hypercube
CONSTRAINT Monotonicity check verifies distance ordering on trajectory pairs

RULES
- On check_non_overlap: sample n_samples intent vectors from unit hypercube, test each against all constraints, CERT_FAIL if any vector activates two or more constraints simultaneously
- On check_layering_order: verify all constraint pairs have explicit LAYER priority declarations, CERT_WARN if any pair missing
- On check_bounded_scope: verify each constraint has finite testable domain with no open-ended semantic predicates, CERT_WARN if unbounded
- On check_monotonicity: sample trajectory pairs where one vector is nearer the boundary, verify distance ordering is preserved, CERT_FAIL if any pair violates ordering
- On run_all: execute all four checks, aggregate results into CBVReport, sign with HMAC
- On CERT_FAIL result: block certification pipeline at step 2b or 2e
- On CERT_WARN result: flag for human review but allow certification to continue

PROCESS
- CBVEngine is instantiated with hmac_key and optional n_samples override
- Caller invokes run_all(constraints) with a list of constraint strings
- check_non_overlap samples random vectors and tests constraint activation
- check_layering_order performs static analysis on constraint pair priorities
- check_bounded_scope scans for open-ended semantic predicates
- check_monotonicity samples trajectory pairs and verifies distance ordering
- CBVReport is assembled with all four CBVResult entries
- CBVReport is HMAC signed over canonical fields
- Signed report is returned for certification pipeline consumption

CHECK
- check_non_overlap on disjoint constraints produces CBVResult with passed True
- check_non_overlap on overlapping constraints produces CERT_FAIL
- check_layering_order on complete layer set produces CBVResult with passed True
- check_bounded_scope on bounded constraints produces CBVResult with passed True
- check_monotonicity on monotonic distances produces CBVResult with passed True
- check_monotonicity on non-monotonic distances produces CERT_FAIL
- run_all returns CBVReport with all four checks and HMAC signature
- TRUST_LEVEL assignment raises AttributeError
- ISOLATION assignment raises AttributeError

WHEN
- certification_step_2b: activate NonOverlapValidation
- certification_step_2c: activate LayeringValidation
- certification_step_2d: activate BoundedScopeValidation
- certification_step_2e: activate MonotonicityValidation

FAILURE
- On overlapping constraints detected: emit CERT_FAIL with violation list
- On missing layer priorities: emit CERT_WARN with missing pair list
- On unbounded constraints detected: emit CERT_WARN with unbounded list
- On monotonicity violation detected: emit CERT_FAIL with violation pairs

CONCEPT NonOverlapValidation
PURPOSE Verify no intent vector activates two or more constraints simultaneously
APPLIES WHEN constraint set has two or more entries
NOT WHEN constraint set is empty or has only one entry
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES list of constraint strings and sample count
EFFECT Overlapping constraint boundaries are detected and reported as CERT_FAIL

CONCEPT LayeringValidation
PURPOSE Verify all constraint pairs have explicit priority ordering
APPLIES WHEN constraint set has two or more entries with potential conflicts
NOT WHEN all constraints operate on disjoint domains
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES list of constraint strings with LAYER declarations
EFFECT Missing priority declarations are reported as CERT_WARN

CONCEPT BoundedScopeValidation
PURPOSE Verify each constraint has finite testable domain
APPLIES WHEN constraint set contains semantic predicates
NOT WHEN all constraints are purely structural
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES list of constraint strings
EFFECT Unbounded constraints are reported as CERT_WARN

CONCEPT MonotonicityValidation
PURPOSE Verify constitutional distance ordering is preserved across trajectory pairs
APPLIES WHEN trajectory samples are available for constraint boundary analysis
NOT WHEN no trajectory data is available
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES trajectory pairs with distance measurements
EFFECT Non-monotonic distance orderings are detected and reported as CERT_FAIL

OUTPUT
- cbv_report: CBVReport with checks list, cert_fail count, cert_warn count, hmac_signature

SUCCESS
non_overlap_validates:      0.25
layering_order_validates:   0.20
bounded_scope_validates:    0.20
monotonicity_validates:     0.25
cannot_mutate_enforced:     0.10
